%N A385602 a(n) is the minimum number of squares from which an n-fold totally concave polyomino (n-TCP) can be made.
%C A385602 a(n) is the solution to the integer non-linear program: min (n + 1)*(x + y) - 1 where x, y are integers such that x>=y, and x*y - (2n + 1)*x - (n + 1)*y - 2n + 1 >= 0.
%H A385602 Vincenzo Librandi, <a href="/A385602/b385602.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A385602 Gill Barequet, Neal Madras, and Johann Peters, <a href="https://cccg-wads-2025.eecs.yorku.ca/cccg-papers/34.pdf">On t-fold Totally-Concave Polyominoes</a>, 37th Can. Conf. Comput. Geometry, Toronto, ON, Canada, Aug. 13-15, 2025, Paper 34.
%H A385602 <a href="/index/Rec#order_03">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (3,-3,1).
%F A385602 a(n) = 6*(n+1)^2-1 for n > 2.
%F A385602 From _Stefano Spezia_, Aug 24 2025: (Start)
%F A385602 G.f.: x*(21 - 13*x + 8*x^2 - 7*x^3 + 3*x^4)/(1 - x)^3.
%F A385602 E.g.f.: exp(x)*(5 + 18*x + 6*x^2) - 5 - 2*x - 3*x^2/2. (End)
%F A385602 a(n) = A140811(n+1) for n>=3. - _Alois P. Heinz_, Sep 15 2025
